Beautiful light along the Kamogawa river near Shimogamo Shrine.
</p>

<p class="jp">
下鴨神社近くの鴨川沿いの美しい光。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Golden Hour" /><category term="Kamo River" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Beautiful light along the Kamogawa river near Shimogamo Shrine.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R06183.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R06183.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Textures・テクスチャー</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241004/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Textures・テクスチャー" /><published>2024-10-04T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-10-04T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/textures</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241004/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Walking around after a rain, I came across this bicycle and wood-clad home.
</p>

<p class="jp">
雨上がりに歩いていると、この自転車と木で覆われた家に出くわした。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Black and White" /><category term="Rain" /><category term="Street" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Walking around after a rain, I came across this bicycle and wood-clad home.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_IMG_0424.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_IMG_0424.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Higanbana・彼岸花</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241001/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Higanbana・彼岸花" /><published>2024-10-01T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-10-01T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/higanbana</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241001/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
It's October, the Sagano fields are being harvested and the smell of smoke is in the air. Farmers often plant Spider Lillies <em>(Higanbana)</em> at the edge of their fields and that's what I was able to photograph today.
</p>

<p class="jp">
10月に入り、嵯峨野の田畑では収穫が進み、燻したような匂いが漂い始めている。農家では田畑の縁に彼岸花を植えることが多く、今日はその写真を撮ることができた。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Flowers" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[It's October, the Sagano fields are being harvested and the smell of smoke is in the air. Farmers often plant Spider Lillies (Higanbana) at the edge of their fields and that's what I was able to photograph today.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R06107.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R06107.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Sanjo Ohashi &amp;amp; Kamogawa・三条大橋と鴨川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240930/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sanjo Ohashi &amp;amp; Kamogawa・三条大橋と鴨川" /><published>2024-09-30T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-09-30T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/sanjo-ohashi</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240930/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The illuminated Sanjo Ohashi Bridge and riverfront restaurants are reflected in the Kamogawa River, against the dark blue sky.
</p>

<p class="jp">
ライトアップされた三条大橋と川沿いのレストランが鴨川に映っている。空は夕暮れの深い青色だ。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Kamo River" /><category term="Bridges" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The illuminated Sanjo Ohashi Bridge and riverfront restaurants are reflected in the Kamogawa River, against the dark blue sky.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2409_A7R06093.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2409_A7R06093.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">The Mothership・宇宙船</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240929/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="The Mothership・宇宙船" /><published>2024-09-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-09-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/spaceship</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240929/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Night view of the Tokyo Metropolitan Gymnasium in Jingu Gaien. Built in 1954, it was used as a venue for the 1964 & 2020 Olympic Games. Rebuilt in the 1980s into the current futuristic design by architect Fumihiko Maki. Shot on Fujicolor Superia 400 film.
</p>

<p class="jp">
神宮外苑の東京体育館の夜景。1954年に建てられ、1964年と2020年のオリンピックの会場として使用された。1980年代に建築家の槇文彦氏によって現在の未来的なデザインに建て直された。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Tokyo" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Film" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Night view of the Tokyo Metropolitan Gymnasium in Jingu Gaien. Built in 1954, it was used as a venue for the 1964 & 2020 Olympic Games. Rebuilt in the 1980s into the current futuristic design by architect Fumihiko Maki. Shot on Fujicolor Superia 400 film.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2409_A7R05902-positive_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2409_A7R05902-positive_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama Fireworks・嵐山花火</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240928/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama Fireworks・嵐山花火" /><published>2024-09-28T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-09-28T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/hanabi</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240928/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A short fireworks set on the bank of Katsura River. Behind is Mt. Arashi and the Togetsu bridge.
</p>

<p class="jp">
桂川の河川敷で打ち上げられる短い花火。背後には嵐山と渡月橋が見える。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Fireworks" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A short fireworks set on the bank of Katsura River. Behind is Mt. Arashi and the Togetsu bridge.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2409_A7R06037_ai-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2409_A7R06037_ai-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kyoto Monochrome・京都モノ語</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240927/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kyoto Monochrome・京都モノ語" /><published>2024-09-27T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-09-27T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/film</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/240927/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Evening on Kiyamachi Street, shot on the classic street photography film, Kodak Tri-X 400.
</p>

